Hey there... You can
hear me, right?

190
00:09:09,666 --> 00:09:12,791
Please tell me you can hear me!

191
00:09:12,875 --> 00:09:14,333
You killed him?

192
00:09:14,416 --> 00:09:15,916
No, but...

193
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:18,416
Wh--
Where uh-- am I?

194
00:09:18,500 --> 00:09:20,291
A-And who am I?

195
00:09:20,375 --> 00:09:23,083
You gave the
guy amnesia?

196
00:09:23,166 --> 00:09:25,166
Okay, then what
happened next?

197
00:09:25,250 --> 00:09:27,333
Well, I decided to
look after the official.

198
00:09:27,416 --> 00:09:29,583
Until the guy's
memory came back.

199
00:09:29,666 --> 00:09:32,500
But it never did, and
eventually, another came by.

200
00:09:32,583 --> 00:09:34,250
He asked me what
happened to the first guy

201
00:09:34,333 --> 00:09:36,750
they sent, and on the spur
of the moment, I said...

202
00:09:36,833 --> 00:09:38,750
Well... That man
was here and he left

203
00:09:38,833 --> 00:09:40,916
this old swordie
on the front porchie.

204
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:43,750
He said "Don't lookie
for me-e" and went bye-bye!

205
00:09:44,291 --> 00:09:45,458
Hey! Wait!

206
00:09:45,541 --> 00:09:49,208
If this story's true.
No! Hold on!

207
00:09:49,291 --> 00:09:50,833
It just can't be true!

208
00:09:50,916 --> 00:09:51,833
[GOZABURO] It is!

209
00:09:51,916 --> 00:09:53,750
That official from
ten years ago?

210
00:09:53,833 --> 00:09:55,208
He's Masa today!

211
00:09:55,291 --> 00:09:57,333
[NAGASUMI] What?

212
00:10:07,958 --> 00:10:09,291
[SUN] Wow, it's been
so long since I

213
00:10:09,375 --> 00:10:11,416
did any sword
practice with ya, Masa!

214
00:10:11,500 --> 00:10:13,041
This'll be fun!

215
00:10:13,125 --> 00:10:14,916
Crap! This definitely
ain't good maggot!

216
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:16,125
Look they're startin'!

217
00:10:16,208 --> 00:10:17,958
Oh no! If Akeno finds
out that Masa's her

218
00:10:18,041 --> 00:10:20,166
long-lost brother
who's still alive...

219
00:10:20,250 --> 00:10:21,333
[AKENO] He won't
be living for much

220
00:10:21,416 --> 00:10:23,208
longer because I'll kill 'em!

221
00:10:23,291 --> 00:10:25,291
It's gonna be
a total bloodbath!

222
00:10:25,375 --> 00:10:26,875
[GOZABURO] We gotta
save Masa's life,

223
00:10:26,958 --> 00:10:28,541
so get in there and make sure
he doesn't remember anythin'!

224
00:10:28,625 --> 00:10:29,666
[NAGASUMI] Me? Hey,
if you hadn't come

225
00:10:29,750 --> 00:10:31,208
up with some crazy
lie to begin with,

226
00:10:31,291 --> 00:10:32,958
we wouldn't be in
this trouble right now!

227
00:10:33,041 --> 00:10:34,666
[GOZABURO] I'd be in bigger
trouble if the authorities

228
00:10:34,750 --> 00:10:35,833
found out that I
punched one of their

229
00:10:35,916 --> 00:10:37,625
officials out and
gave him amnesia!

230
00:10:37,708 --> 00:10:40,000
[NAGASUMI] And by doing that,
you ruined the guy's life!

231
00:10:40,083 --> 00:10:41,875
[GOZABURO (baby talk)] I
made a big booboo there.

232
00:10:41,958 --> 00:10:44,541
I'm so-wwy; very so-wwy.
Pwease help me fix it.

233
00:10:44,625 --> 00:10:45,583
[NAGASUMI] This guy.

234
00:10:45,666 --> 00:10:46,791
[MASA] Akeno...

235
00:10:46,875 --> 00:10:49,208
May I? I'd like to see
your sword, please.

236
00:10:49,541 --> 00:10:51,375
For some reason, it's
had a strange pull

237
00:10:51,458 --> 00:10:53,625
on me since I laid eyes on it.

238
00:10:54,041 --> 00:10:55,250
All right then.

239
00:10:59,708 --> 00:11:01,375
[GOZABURO AND NAGASUMI]
Thump thump thump thump thump!

240
00:11:01,458 --> 00:11:02,750
The way it feels...

241
00:11:02,833 --> 00:11:04,958
Like there's something
familiar about it.

